<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Patch>

	<!-- ============================================================================
	     GTI Infinite Turrets - consumption-only approach (THEORY TEST BUILD)

	     Goal: every turret/mortar/rocket launcher has infinite ammo.

	     Approach: instead of REMOVING CompProperties_Refuelable (which broke the
	     rocketswarm launcher - its top sprite + Building_TurretRocket activation are
	     driven by that comp, so removing it null-derefs during draw, invisible turret),
	     we leave all comps intact and simply zero out per-shot consumption.

	     Why this should be enough: every vanilla turret spawns full
	     (initialFuelPercent=1) and only depletes via consumeFuelPerShot. Set that to 0
	     and the barrel/rockets never drain, so ammo is effectively infinite, with no
	     exclusions and nothing going invisible.

	     In vanilla 1.6 ONLY turret/mortar/rocketswarm weapon defs use consumeFuelPerShot
	     (verified: Data/Core/.../Buildings_Security_Turrets.xml is the only file that
	     contains it), so the broad xpath below is safe and also catches modded turrets.

	     WHAT TO WATCH FOR WHILE TESTING (does keeping the comp break anything?):
	       1. Rocketswarm launcher is now VISIBLE and fires repeatedly after cooldown. (fix)
	       2. Standard turrets fire forever; their fuel/"barrel durability" bar sits at 100%.
	       3. Uninstall a turret (minify) and re-install it: does it come back full and
	          combat-ready, or does it demand a fresh barrel/refuel? If it demands refuel,
	          the comp was "more than cosmetic" and we should go back to removing it
	          (structurally, excluding thingClass="Building_TurretRocket").
	       4. No red errors in the dev log on load or when turrets fire.
	     ============================================================================ -->

	<Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace">
		<success>Always</success>
		<xpath>Defs/ThingDef/verbs/li/consumeFuelPerShot</xpath>
		<value>
			<consumeFuelPerShot>0</consumeFuelPerShot>
		</value>
	</Operation>

</Patch>
